SIMPLE: indignity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indignity
<hw>In*dig"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Indignities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>indignitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indignit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Indign</er>.]</ety> <def>Any action toward another which manifests
contempt for him; an offense against personal dignity; unmerited
contemptuous treatment; contumely; incivility or injury, accompanied
with insult.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How might a prince of my great hopes forget⟦br⟧
So great <qex>indignities</qex> you laid upon me?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A person of so great place and worth constrained to endure so foul
<qex>indignities</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indignly</ent>⟦br⟧
